               <floruit notBefore="1450" notAfter="1508">.
                  <persName ref="PRS1848AmdaMi">ʾAmda Mikāʾel</persName>
                  was an influential political figure from the reign of 
                  <persName ref="PRS10626ZaraY">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>  Zarʾa Yāʿqob</persName> 
                  to that of                  <persName ref="PRS7481NaodA">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>
                      Nāʿod (ʾAnbasā Baḍar)</persName>. 
                  He was appointed as <persName ref="PRS1848AmdaMi">
                     <roleName type="title">malkaññā</roleName>  
                  </persName>by  
                  <persName ref="PRS10626ZaraY">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> Zarʾa Yāʿqob</persName> over all of <placeName ref="LOC3061Fataga">Faṭagār</placeName>.
                  <persName ref="PRS1848AmdaMi">ʾAmda Mikāʾel</persName> is most remembered for the role he played in determining the successors 
                  to                  <persName ref="PRS2334BaedaM">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>
                      Baʾǝda Māryām I</persName>,  
                
                  <persName ref="PRS3874eskender">  
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> ʾƎskǝndǝr</persName>, 
               
                  <persName ref="PRS1855Amdase">   
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> ʾAmda Ṣǝyon II</persName>
                    
                    and <persName ref="PRS7481NaodA">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> Nāʿod (ʾAnbasā Baḍar)</persName>. </floruit>
          
               
               
